result.name: Cheung Kei Cafe

reviews.text: Below average in service, food quality, cooking for a neighborhood cha-chan-ting.

I hope nobody goes through the same experiences as I had with this cafe. 

Went there and ordered a salt & pepper pork chop as takeout and when I came home, to my surprise, it was all bones with little meat attached. My initial thought was that it was more like a meal for dogs. Spare rib isn't even on their menu. I paid 61HKD for the meal and they can't serve me something proper. I don't know how they expect customers to be satisfied with their service. Lacks integrity and responsibility. 

1/5 will not go again.

希望無其他人比佢地掠水。
去叫左個椒鹽豬扒外賣，返到屋企先發覺佢比哂啲骨我。似狗飯多過人飯。佢地餐牌又無椒鹽排骨嘅。
睇佢裝修得靚靚原來咁古惑。

請大家唔好比佢騙。
Fresh Made Chinese bread with great taste which seldom could be found nowadays, Good coffee and comfortable seats
Milk tea and bread are good

result.name: 祥基茶餐廳

reviews.text: 一間新裝修的舊式茶餐廳，食物款式大多是大路款式，冇乜撚手小菜，但呢個就是它們的優點，平平凡凡，永遠都能提供普普通通，但又好親切的菜式。
暫時只試過兩次下午茶餐 但是味道都不錯 份量充足（對我來說） 有空再補回相片～
招呼好、服務快！平、靚、正、好味！
一般港式茶餐廳，很就腳，地點方便
健身室清潔，不過較細，有免費泊車。
